Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle, rising to sharpish turn, of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Teisagoras. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 322.19.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (273)
